# Enterprise Security. One Stack.

XCloak is an open-core security platform that replaces a rack of siloed tools with a single coherent system. SIEM, EDR, NGFW, SOAR, Threat Intelligence, and Mobile MDM — all sharing the same data model, the same alert pipeline, and the same response engine.

Built with Go and Flutter. No Java. No per-seat licensing for the core. Self-hostable in 5 minutes.

[Get Started →](https://docs.xcloak.tech/getting-started) [GitHub →](https://github.com/The-Abhishek1/XCLOAK-SECURITY-SUITE) [Live Demo →](#)

---

## Why XCloak?

Most security stacks are assembled from a dozen tools that were never designed to work together. Alert fatigue, integration debt, and licensing costs compound every year.

XCloak is purpose-built as a unified platform. When a YARA match fires on an endpoint, the incident is automatically correlated with network events, enriched with Active Directory context, and a response playbook is triggered — all without touching five different consoles.

---

## Capabilities

### SIEM — Know What's Happening

Log everything, detect everything. XCloak ingests from agents, syslog (UDP/TCP), HTTP endpoints, and cloud connectors — and runs 12 behavioral detection engines continuously.

- **43 production-ready Sigma rules** seeded automatically on first run, spanning Initial Access through Impact
- **Kafka-backed async pipeline** — IOC matching and enrichment happen off the request path
- **Elasticsearch dual-write** for fast full-text log search across your entire fleet
- **Unified log normalizer** — CEF, LEEF, JSON, NDJSON, and plain syslog all parsed into the same `ParsedFields` schema

### EDR — See Every Endpoint

The XCloak Go agent is a single binary with no runtime dependencies. It collects 15 autonomous telemetry streams on both Linux and Windows — and ships everything back to the platform in real time.

| What the agent sees | Linux | Windows |
|--------------------|-------|---------|
| Processes (PID, PPID, cmdline, exe) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Network connections with PID mapping | ✅ `/proc/net` | ✅ netstat+tasklist |
| Users (groups, sudo, SSH keys, last login) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Installed packages (dpkg/rpm/pip/snap/winget) | ✅ | ✅ |
| File integrity (hash + mode + owner + mtime) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Cron jobs / Scheduled Tasks | ✅ | ✅ |
| Kernel modules / Drivers | ✅ | ✅ |
| SUID/SGID binary inventory | ✅ | — |
| Disk usage per mount | ✅ | ✅ |
| eBPF TCP events (real-time) | ✅ kernel 5.8+ | — |

### NGFW — Detect Network Threats

Twelve behavioral detection engines run continuously against your log stream, each mapped to a MITRE ATT&CK technique:

| Engine | What it catches |
|--------|----------------|
| **C2 Beacon Detector** | Periodic outbound connections with suspicious timing regularity |
| **DNS Security** | DGA/entropy analysis, DNS tunneling, query floods |
| **Port Scan / Lateral Movement** | Vertical, horizontal, SYN sweeps; SMB spray |
| **Data Exfiltration** | Volume floods, cloud storage drain (S3/Drive/OneDrive/Dropbox) |
| **TLS/JA3 Fingerprinting** | 13+ C2 tool fingerprints — Cobalt Strike, Sliver, Havoc, BruteRatel, Emotet |
| **Credential Attacks** | SSH/RDP brute force, password spray, credential stuffing |
| **Privilege Escalation** | Windows Event IDs 4728/4732/4720/4672; Linux sudo/SUID chains |
| **Ransomware Behavior** | FIM mass-modification + crypto extensions; vssadmin/bcdedit kill-chain |
| **Living-off-the-Land** | Office→PowerShell chains; certutil, mshta, bitsadmin, regsvr32 abuse |
| **Impossible Travel** | Login from 900+ km/h distance (haversine + GeoIP) |
| **UEBA** | Per-user behavioral baseline; anomaly scoring |
| **Network Behavior Analytics** | Baseline deviation, anomalous connection patterns |

### SOAR — Respond Automatically

Automated playbooks close the gap between detection and response. Every destructive action goes through a human-approval gate before the agent acts.

- **AI-recommended playbooks** — Claude or Ollama suggests response chains based on MITRE context
- **FIM + YARA auto-quarantine** — critical file modifications automatically create approval tasks
- **Script runner** — run bash/python3 on any enrolled agent with real-time output
- **Deception technology** — honeypots, canary tokens, decoy files and users
- **15-minute stale task expiry** — destructive tasks auto-expire if an approver doesn't act

### Threat Intelligence

- **Sigma rules** — import custom rules from the community or write your own
- **YARA rules** — malware signature scanning with auto-quarantine on match
- **IOC engine** — IP, domain, hash, URL, email indicators matched async via Kafka
- **STIX/TAXII, MISP, AlienVault OTX** feed connectors
- **Threat actor profiles** — TTPs, attribution, associated IOCs
- **JA3 fingerprint blocklist** — updated list of known malicious TLS fingerprints

### MDM — Secure Mobile Devices

The XCloak Agent Android app is a full MDM client and SOC admin console in one. Enroll any Android device and get real-time security posture, app inventory, and remote management — without Google EMM or per-device licensing.

**24 posture fields collected on every check-in:**
Root detection · Developer options · USB debugging · Unknown sources · Battery level/charging · Storage total/free · RAM · Network type · VPN detection · Security patch level · Manufacturer · Build fingerprint

**10 MDM commands:**
`collect_posture` · `collect_apps` · `scan_threats` · `collect_logs` · `sync` · `message` · `rotate_token` · `update_agent` · `lock_screen` (Device Owner) · `wipe` (Device Owner)

